<h4>Q: What ? Computer moderated with Dice - How does that possibly work?</h4>
<p>For each combat situation that occurs in the game, the computer asks a series of straight forward questions, and then presents the commanding player with a set of choices to make, and roughly what the odds of success of each choice are.</p>
<p>The defending player in this combat situation must answer the same questions, and may also be asked to decide on a reaction choice to make to counter the commanding player's move.</p>
<p>Once all the inputs for the situation are entered by BOTH players, the Computer Umpire generates a simple table of results from a D6, and shows this results table to BOTH affected players.</p>
<p>The commanding player rolls the dice. Both players then click the appropriate number that matches the die roll, (and when both the inputs agree), the results are applied.</p>

