<h3>Tech Questions</h3>
<hr>
<h4>Q: What is this ? Is it another computer game or something?</h4>
<p>Yes, its a game, Yes, there are computers involved, but No ... its neither of the above !</p>
<p>This is a completely analog Tabletop Miniatures Game ... in the full traditional sense - with miniatures, scenery, tapes and rulers, and players who must interact face to face.</p>
<p>The "Computer" part of it takes on the role of a sort of combined Game Umpire / Bookkeeper for the action on the tabletop. Its there to assist, handle the information flow, and manage the bookkeeping.</p>
<p>Each player uses their own computer device (laptop / phone / tablet), to interact with the "Computer Umpire" using a standard Web Browser interface whilst playing the game.<p>
<p>So, not a computer game .. but a computer-assisted miniatures game, with a web interface.</p>

